\title{ecoregionr: Environmental Bioregionalization and Clustering Toolkit}
\description{
`ecoregionr` provides a complete, reproducible pipeline for delineating
environmental bioregions from polygon shapefiles and raster covariates.
Two clustering strategies are implemented:

\describe{
  \item{PCA + k-means (unconstrained)}{
    Maximises within-cluster environmental homogeneity without any spatial
    constraint.  Best for scientific exploration and multi-country
    comparisons.  Entry point: \code{\link{run_clustering}}.
  }
  \item{SKATER (spatially constrained)}{
    Enforces geographic contiguity — every bioregion is a connected region.
    Best for operational planning and field surveillance zone design.
    Entry point: \code{\link{run_skater_clustering}}.
  }
}
}
\section{Typical workflow}{

\enumerate{
  \item \code{\link{extract_continuous_stats}} — summarise continuous
    rasters (elevation, population, …) per polygon.
  \item \code{\link{extract_categorical_composition}} — compute land-cover
    and climate proportions per polygon.
  \item \code{\link{build_cluster_table}} — join all covariates into one
    wide table.
  \item \code{\link{impute_medians}} — fill missing values.
  \item \code{\link{run_clustering}} **or** \code{\link{run_skater_clustering}}
    — cluster the polygons.
  \item \code{\link{build_leaflet_map}} / \code{\link{make_static_map}} —
    visualise results.
  \item \code{\link{generate_cluster_paragraphs}} — auto-generate
    natural-language descriptions.
}
}

\section{Built-in lookup tables}{

\describe{
  \item{\code{ecoregionr:::kg_lookup}}{
    Named character vector mapping integer raster codes to
    Köppen-Geiger climate class names (30 classes).
  }
  \item{\code{ecoregionr:::lc_lookup}}{
    Named character vector mapping integer raster codes to
    ESRI 10 m land-cover class names (9 classes).
  }
}
